,"marks":1,"options":["Pulmonary hypertension","Smooth muscle hypertrophy","Reduced lung compliance","Fibrosis of lung tissue","Mucus hypersecretion"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn emphysema, destruction of alveolar walls leads to loss of elastic recoil and permanent enlargement of airspaces. The destruction of the pulmonary capillary bed combined with hypoxic vasoconstriction leads to \u003Cstrong\u003Epulmonary hypertension\u003C/strong\u003E, which is a major complication affecting right heart function.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003Esmooth muscle hypertrophy\u003C/strong\u003E can occur in airways disease, it is more characteristic of asthma. \u003Cstrong\u003EReduced lung compliance\u003C/strong\u003E is not typically seen in emphysema; in fact, lung compliance is increased due to loss of elastic recoil. \u003Cstrong\u003EFibrosis of lung tissue\u003C/strong\u003E is not a typical feature of emphysema, which is characterized by tissue destruction rather than fibrosis. \u003Cstrong\u003EMucus hypersecretion\u003C/strong\u003E is more characteristic of chronic bronchitis rather than emphysema.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Emphysema leads to pulmonary hypertension due to destruction of capillary beds and hypoxic vasoconstriction","Emphysema is characterized by permanent enlargement of airspaces and destruction of alveolar walls","Secondary pulmonary hypertension is a major complication that affects right heart function"],"references":["Agust\u00ed AG. Systemic effects of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease. Proc Am Thorac Soc. 2005;2(4):367-70; discussion 371-2. doi: 10.1513/pats.200504-026SR. PMID: 16267364.","Calverley PMA, Walker PP. Contemporary Concise Review 2022: Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease. Respirology. 2023 May;28(5):428-436. doi: 10.1111/resp.14489. Epub 2023 Mar 15. PMID: 36922031.","Shrikrishna D, Hopkinson NS. Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease: consequences beyond the lung. Clin Med (Lond). 2012 Feb;12(1):71-4. doi: 10.7861/clinmedicine.12-1-71. PMID: 22372229; PMCID: PMC4953427.","Pahal P, Avula A, Sharma S. Emphysema. [Updated 2023 Jan 26]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482217/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51272"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15509"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51272","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51272"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-27T09:03:24+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-27T09:05:26+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8200"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65827"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","li